<br>
Anyway normal hotkey <br>
<br>
/autoattack off<br>
/pause<br>
/doability x (fiegn)<br>
/sit off<br>
/autoattack on<br>
<br>
after alittle testing the 0 second pause makes sure attack is off when u fiegn. although im not there yet i can lose 0 damage with gsc/jm or baton of faith or fists while using this, and i would love for someone to try this with double epic fists to guarantee it works (i know it does)<br>
<br>
the great thing about this hotkey is you still do melee damage even though u see yourself laying on the ground.<br>
<br>
any comments on this are appreciated<br>
<br>
PS-if using on big mobs and fiegn fails, turn off attack and step back because you have to wait for feign to recycle and on raids sometimes you need to drop aggro.<br>
<br>
Dacommon 53 taxi of Bushido Clan<br>
Karkern 49 puller of Bushido Clan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiskys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/8/02 2:03:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=997.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: real evade key</span><hr size=1> I just get used to do the key sequence :<br>
<br>
Q , 1, 4, Q<br>
<br>
(Q for attack on / off) (1 for feign death) (4 for sit / stand) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uindicus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Indicus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/10/02 8:30:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=997.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: real evade key</span><hr size=1> I've had a hotbutton labeled EVADE with this same setup in use for some time now, works great as a quick aggro reducer, and is almost unnoticeable to me.<br>
