<red>~Grim</red></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugrimfeather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimfeather</A> at: 8/1/02 8:08:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 4:51:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=997.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: real evade key</span><hr size=1> It works great for me - I've never had a pause in my &quot;evade&quot; FD hotkey and it seems to work regardless of what weapon/s I'm using.<br>
<br>
It takes the pain out of the regular FDs often needed to keep aggro on tanks, and makes it easier to &quot;evade&quot; aggro onto a druid, necro etc. if you're helping them kite outdoors.<br>
<br>
If you FD while in a group attacking a high level mob, it reduces its hate for you a little but if you're still in melee range and on top of its hate list it'll carry on attacking; regular FDs are therefore vital to stay well down the hate list if you have a weak taunting or defensive disc tank, or if MT transitions are expected in raids.<br>
<br>
Hitting while apparently FD is just due to delay on the animation.  A side effect is that werewolf form's long dying animation (during which you're rooted to the spot and can't move or turn) interferes badly with using FD for aggro control; you can find the mob's been pushed well out of melee range several seconds before you can move to catch up with it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A> at: 8/2/02 5:15:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usarphs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarphs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 10:19:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=997.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: real evade key</span><hr size=1> FD does not reduce hate. It is all or nothing.  If a mob seems to lose some interest in you, its because you stopped attacking it. <p>Sarphus<br>
Bard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 5:01:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=997.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Absolutely FD reduces hate</span><hr size=1> And it reduces it by quite a bit, too.  Here's a simple test you can do, too.  Get two monks.  Both attack.  Unless you have identical monks, one will get more agro.  Both turn off attack.  One with agro FDs then stands (ie. evades).  The MOB will switch to the other one and it will take a fair effort to regain agro again.  This will happen every single time, not just when you get a luckly blur.<br>
<br>
Using an evade key on raids, I'm near the top of the damage list for monks, but always the last one to get agro.  The only monks higher on the damage list are those with better weapons.  Evade key is truly awesome for large fights. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
